# Mobile CSS breakpoint order

For this Shopify theme, write desktop/base styles first, then add mobile overrides at the end of the CSS file.

- Put mobile media queries at the end of the file, not scattered throughout.
- Use this order:
  1. `@media (max-width: 996px)` for tablet and down.
  2. `@media (max-width: 480px)` for small mobile and down.
- Keep the `480px` block after the `996px` block so narrower overrides can refine broader mobile rules.

```css
.component {
  /* Desktop/base styles first */
  padding: 2rem;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

@media (max-width: 996px) {
  .component {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .component {
    padding: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
}
```
